---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Hey, I'm Justin; aka Flabbyaxe. Welcome to my corner of the internet."
	pubDate={new Date('May 27 2026')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Hey there! I'm Justin, though around the internet you might know me as <strong>Flabbyaxe</strong>. 
		Depending on who you ask, what I "do" might get you a different answer, but the way I'd put it 
		is that I'm an aspiring tech worker who's figuring it out one problem at a time.
	</p>

	<p>
		If there's one thing that defines me, it's that once I set my mind to something, I'm seeing it 
		through. Whether it's debugging something that's been driving me up the wall, nailing a new recipe, 
		or finally summiting a trail I've been eyeing, I'm the kind of person who likes to get things 
		<em>fixed</em> and get things <em>done</em>.
	</p>

	<p>
		When I'm not knee-deep in tech stuff, you'll probably find me in the kitchen experimenting with 
		something new, out on a trail somewhere, setting up camp under the stars, rolling dice at a 
		Dungeons & Dragons table, or losing track of time in a good video game. Yeah, the usual.
	</p>

	<p>
		So why the blog? Honestly, I wanted to stand out a little. There's a lot of noise out there, and 
		I figured the best way to cut through it was to just share what I actually know, what I've actually 
		run into, and how I worked through it. If something tripped me up and I found a way past it, chances 
		are someone else is hitting the same wall — and maybe something I write saves them a few hours of 
		frustration.
	</p>

	<p>
		Whether you're here for the tech, the personal stuff, or you just stumbled in: Welcome! 
		Hope you find something useful, or at least something worth reading. Stick around.
	</p>
</Layout>